# EnvelopeOS — Requirements Clarification

> Pre-build clarification doc. Staff-solutions-architect lens. No code yet. Goal: surface every meaningful design decision before the ISA is written.

## 1. Summary of understanding

Nick wants a zero-based envelope budgeting layer on top of his existing PocketSmith setup, because Dave Ramsey's apps do not connect to Australian banks and PocketSmith's envelope handling is weak. PocketSmith stays as the bank-feed and categorisation layer (ANZ primary account, NAB credit card, Macquarie account); a new app owns the envelope semantics (allocation, cash basis, monthly and annualised budgets prorated to month, time-travel views of envelope balances at any past date). UI must work on web and mobile. Sync from PocketSmith is undecided between API, periodic CSV export/import, and PAI Interceptor scraping. The envelope state should feed the PAI Pulse dashboard. This is personal financial data, so security is a first-class constraint.

The trick of this project is that "zero-based envelope budgeting" is a specific methodology with specific edge cases (credit card spend, refunds, transfers between envelopes, mid-month income, annualised budgets, rollovers) and the build will live or die on whether the model matches Nick's mental model exactly. Most of the questions in section 6 exist to nail that down.

